{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Retarget provider shims to AGENTS.md + repo-wide reference sweep + optional per-tool pointers\n\n## Why\n\nOnce `AGENTS.md` is canonical, the existing shims and scattered `CLAUDE.md` references must be\nreconciled so nothing points at stale guidance, and we should decide which (if any) low-cost\nper-tool pointer files are worth adding. `.codex/config.toml` currently falls back to `CLAUDE.md`\nwith a comment saying it's temporary \"until the guidance is migrated\" ÔÇö this story completes that\nmigration. `.agents/rules/rebar.md` is a hand-maintained neutral distillation that must not drift\nfrom the new `AGENTS.md`.\n\n## What\n\n(1) Update `.codex/config.toml` so Codex reads `AGENTS.md` natively (remove/adjust the CLAUDE.md\nfallback and the \"temporary shim\" comment). (2) Reconcile `.agents/rules/rebar.md` with the new\n`AGENTS.md` (reduce to a pointer or align content; eliminate drift). (3) Sweep the repo for\n`CLAUDE.md` references (`CONTRIBUTING.md`, `docs/`, `README.md`, tests, `.github/workflows/`) and\nupdate each to the new structure ÔÇö or confirm it intentionally targets the thin file. (4) Decide\nand record whether to add optional per-tool pointers: `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (for\nCopilot IN-EDITOR) and a Gemini `context.fileName` note; any added must be pointers to `AGENTS.md`,\nnot duplicated content. Keep the module-size gate and all CI green.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `.codex/config.toml`, `.agents/rules/rebar.md`, reference updates across docs/CONTRIBUTING/\nREADME/tests/CI, and optional pointer files. Out: the root-file and template changes (their own\nstories). Depends on: the AGENTS.md story and the CLAUDE.local.md story (sweep runs after the\ncanonical files exist).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `.codex/config.toml` reads `AGENTS.md` natively; the \"temporary/until migrated\" wording is\n  gone.\n  - Proving: `rg -c 'CLAUDE.md|temporary' .codex/config.toml` reflects the completed migration.\n- [ ] `.agents/rules/rebar.md` is consistent with `AGENTS.md` (pointer or aligned), no drift.\n- [ ] Every remaining `CLAUDE.md` reference in the repo is intentional or updated.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'CLAUDE\\.md' --glob '!CLAUDE.md'` reviewed line-by-line in the change.\n- [ ] Decision on optional Copilot/Cursor/Gemini per-tool files is recorded; any added are\n  pointers, not duplicated content.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` pass and the module-size CI gate is green.\n\n## De-risking results (zero code impact; concrete surface)\n\n**The CLAUDE.md Ôćĺ AGENTS.md rename breaks ZERO code.** Every `src/` match is either the\nunrelated env var `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` (`session_log.py`, `session_id.py`,\n`transition_close.py`) or prose: `_processors.py:307` (comment), `rebar.toml:3` (comment).\n**No `.github/workflows` reference.** Real reference surface is ~15 files (excludes the\n`.rebar/cache/`, `bridge_state/snapshots/`, and `docs/experiments/` corpus, which are data):\nCONTRIBUTING.md, README.md, CHANGELOG.md, rebar.toml, and\ndocs/{architecture,event-schema,exit-codes,api-stability,jira-sync-setup,llm-framework,\nplan-review-criteria-guide,releasing,workflow-editor,workflow-engine}.md, adr/0043.\n\n**Also update the plan-review CRITERIA text** so the gate's own coaching points at the new file:\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json:407` and\n`src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md:10` cite \"an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc\" Ôćĺ change\nto reference `AGENTS.md`. **Codex:** `.codex/config.toml`'s\n`project_doc_fallback_filenames=[\"CLAUDE.md\"]` becomes moot once `AGENTS.md` exists (Codex reads\nAGENTS.md natively as primary); update the \"temporaryÔÇŽuntil migrated\" comment (lines 3-6) rather\nthan relying on the fallback.\n\nRevised Acceptance Criteria:\n- [ ] `rg -n 'CLAUDE\\.md' --glob '!CLAUDE.md'` reviewed line-by-line; each remaining reference is\n  intentional or updated to AGENTS.md.\n- [ ] The plan-review criteria text (criteria_routing.json + plan_review_T5e.md) and the\n  `.codex/config.toml` comment are updated to the completed-migration state.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` pass and the module-size CI gate is green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784232656635668001,"uuid":"a3f3e826-0acb-4ba6-9c61-6944dce424e0"}